CASE00001.summary:
## Clinical Case Summary Analysis (3 Similar Cases)

### Classification Pattern
- **Predominant Classification**: Normal (3/3 cases)
- All demonstrate Category 1 (reassuring) CTG patterns with favorable outcomes

### CTG Pattern Characteristics
- **Average Baseline FHR**: 131.7 bpm (normal range 110-160 bpm)
- **Average Variability (ASTV)**: 57.6 ms (excellent fetal oxygenation)
- **Average Accelerations**: 2.567/sec (present and reassuring)
- No significant decelerations observed across cases

### Common Risk Factors
- Low-risk pregnancies

### Outcomes & Management
- **Delivery Methods**: Assisted vaginal, Spontaneous vaginal
- **NICU Admissions**: 0/3 cases
- **Average Apgar Scores**: 1-min: 8.7, 5-min: 10.0

### Key Clinical Insights
- These cases exemplify reassuring CTG patterns with excellent neonatal outcomes
- High variability (>58ms) correlates strongly with favorable outcomes
- Presence of accelerations indicates fetal well-being
- Conservative management with routine monitoring appropriate
- Average gestational age: 38.4 weeks
